<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,152,719]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,330,615,641]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Discussion</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="W. T. Wang, Y. G. Wei &amp; A. K. Monro" authorityYear="2011" box="[367,717,616,641]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Urticaceae" genus="Elatostema" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="retrorstrigulosum">
<emphasis box="[367,717,616,641]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Elatostema retrorstrigulosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Gagnepain (1929)" authorityName="Gagnepain" authorityYear="1929" box="[957,1435,616,642]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Urticaceae" genus="Elatostema" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="balansae">
<emphasis box="[957,1206,616,641]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Elatostema balansae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gagnepain, F." box="[1219,1435,616,642]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="80 - 82" refId="ref10041" refString="Gagnepain, F. (1929) Quelques Elatostema et un Procris nouveaux d'Indo-Chine. Bulletin de la Societe Botanique de France 76: 80 - 82." type="journal article" year="1929">Gagnepain (1929)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from which it can be distinguished based on stem, leaf and staminate inflorescence and flower morphology, leaf, stipule, staminate receptacle and flower morphology as summarised in the table below:
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<table box="[155,1417,788,1047]" gridcols="3" gridrows="6" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<tr box="[155,1417,788,812]" gridrow="0" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" rowspan-0="1">
<td box="[497,883,788,812]" gridcol="1" gridrow="0" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName authorityName="W. T. Wang, Y. G. Wei &amp; A. K. Monro" authorityYear="2011" box="[497,821,788,812]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Urticaceae" genus="Elatostema" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="retrorstrigulosum">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[497,821,788,812]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Elatostema retrorstrigulosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</td>
<td box="[951,1417,788,812]" gridcol="2" gridrow="0" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gagnepain" authorityYear="1929" box="[952,1180,788,812]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Urticaceae" genus="Elatostema" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="balansae">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[952,1180,788,812]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Elatostema balansae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</td>
</tr>
<tr box="[155,1417,828,886]" gridrow="1" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<td box="[155,435,828,886]" gridcol="0" gridrow="1" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Stem pubescence</td>
<td box="[497,883,828,886]" gridcol="1" gridrow="1" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">densely pubescent, the hairs retrorse</td>
